      <div class="msgContentFrame">Actually, a similar concept to a sphere theater like the one in FFX sounds awesome. Buy cutscenes and music tracks you've seen with gil, be able to play them, etc. <br /> <br />And yes please to actual quests and lots of wonderful storyline! S.O.B. quests, much of Windurst's quests, WoTG quests, three men in a closet, all sorts of things in FFXI had terrible monetary rewards but some of the best rewards of all: being highly entertained and putting a smile on your face at times, making your day all better! <br /> <br />Of course, I'm sure with time we will actually see real quests and lots of them. Just look at FFXI. The first original quests, were pretty boring and hardly better than levequests for a lot. &quot;I want some flint stones for a fire. Oh hey, you got them. thanks.&quot; But as you start doing RoTZ quests, you start seeing a lot of quests with actual storyline instead of &quot;go fetch me this, thanks&quot; quests, and by CoP they start getting pretty epic. ToAU quests and WoTG ones in particular oftentimes outshone even CoP quests, which was something I didn't think possible till I started doing them. The adventures of Babban, three men in a closet, the serpent general quests, and more were all ones I absolutely was impressed with, when I wasn't busy trying to keep my gut from tearing apart with laughter. <br /> <br />MOAR QUESTS WITH REAL STORY, SE! <div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Main Character: Psion <br />World: Phoenix <br />Resident of Windurst <br />75BLU/75PUP/70COR <br /><a href="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?186284" title="http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?186284" rel="external">http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?186284</a> </div></div>
