      <div class="msgContentFrame">I think adding more cutscenes would actually make you feel like your participating.  FFXI had cutscenes even for &quot;small&quot; quests, which added to the immersion into the world.  Having a small written blurb on levequests is insufficient to accomplish this.  Yes, it is faster to complete the levequests this way (presumably geared to the &quot;casual&quot; players), but there is no real sense of accomplishment, and they aren't really that fun. <br /> <br />I'm fine with leaving the levequests the way they are, but add real quests as well.  Sometimes I log in and I plan to grind through leves, but other times I really would like there to be more of an adventure to the time I spend in game.  Right now the sense of adventure in FFXIV is pretty minimal.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><b><a href="HTTP://ffxicutscenes.blogspot.com/" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxicutscenes.blogspot.com/">CoP, ZM, ToAU, WotG mission/quest Videos</a></b> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/482404.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
